        <input type="number" id="sizeKB" placeholder="Enter size in KB">
      </div>
      <button id="resizeBtn" class="btn">Resize Image</button>
      <div id="result" class="result">Upload an image and enter target size.</div>
      <img id="preview" class="preview" src="" alt="">

      <h4 class="h4-style">About This Tool</h4>
      <p class="justify-p">
        This tool allows you to quickly resize images directly in your browser to a specific KB size. It works locally, so your files remain private and secure.
      </p>
      <h4 class="h4-style">How to Use</h4>
      <p class="justify-p">
        Upload an image, enter the desired target size in KB, and click "Resize Image". After resizing, the button changes to "Reset", allowing you to start over. You will see a preview and download link immediately.
      </p>
      <h4 class="h4-style">Note</h4>
      <p class="justify-p">
